OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FNine men from Derry have spent almost
OL,7,Ftwo years on trial at Belfast Crown
OL,8,FCourt on a total of 52 charges arising
OL,9,Ffrom both the riot on April 18, 2019
OL,10,Fand street disorder in Derry two days
OL,11,Fbeforehand.
OL,13,FThree defendants have been charged
OL,14,Fwith murdering Ms McKee, possessing a
OL,15,Ffirearm and ammunition and other
OL,16,Flinked offences including rioting and
OL,17,Fboth possessing and throwing petrol
OL,18,Fbombs.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FThey are not alleged to have fired the
OL,7,Fgun used to kill Ms McKee but with
OL,8,Fintentionally encouraging or assisting
OL,9,Fthe gunman on a joint enterprise basis.
OL,11,FThe trio are Paul McIntyre (58) from
OL,12,FKells Walk, 25-year old Jordan Devine
OL,13,Ffrom Bishop Street and Peter Cavanagh
OL,14,F(37) from Mary Street.
OL,16,FTheir co-accused were charged with
OL,17,Foffences including rioting and
OL,18,Fthrowing petrol bombs.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FThey are Christopher Gillen (45) from
OL,7,FBalbane Pass, Joseph Campbell (25)
OL,8,Ffrom Gosheden Cottages, 34-year old
OL,9,FPatrick Gallagher from John Field
OL,10,FPlace, Jude McCrory (28) from Gartan
OL,11,FSquare, Joseph Barr (37) from
OL,12,FSandringham Drive, 57-year old Kieran
OL,13,FMcCool from Ballymagowan Gardens.
OL,15,FA tenth defendant, 58-year old William
OL,16,FElliot from Ballymagowan Garden in
OL,17,FDerry, passed away in England in last
OL,18,FFebruary.
OL,20,FAll nine accused have denied the
OL,21,Fcharges levelled against them.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FBefore she reserved judgement, Mrs
OL,7,FJustice Smyth was addressed again by
OL,8,FMark Mulholland KC, who is
OL,9,Frepresenting Paul McIntyre and who
OL,10,Fspend a second day making final oral
OL,11,Fsubmissions.
OL,13,FWhilst he branded Ms McKee's death as
OL,14,F"a tragedy", Mr Mulholland spoke of
OL,15,F"fragile strands" in a case he
OL,16,Fdescribed as "circumstantial."
OL,18,FThis, he said, included "generic
OL,19,Fclothing comparison evidence" and a
OL,20,Flack of identification evidence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FMr Mulholland said that following Ms
OL,7,FMcKee's death police "quite properly"
OL,8,Femployed all their reserves and "left
OL,9,Fno stone unturned in the course of
OL,10,Ftheir investigation" - but that this
OL,11,Famounted to rounding up "all the usual
OL,12,Fsuspects."
OL,14,FThe defence barrister said "the
OL,15,Fproblem with that" was that some
OL,16,Fofficers went "outside their duties",
OL,17,Fhe claimed "lines were crossed" and
OL,18,Fsaid that during the trial expert
OL,19,Fwitnesses were "compromised".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1776445554
OL,3,CJudgement reserved in murder trial of
OL,4,Cjournalist Lyra McKee
OL,6,FCiting "inconsistencies", Mr
OL,7,FMulholland said: "We urge and
OL,8,Frespectfully invite the court to
OL,9,Facquit the accused Mr McIntyre."
OL,11,FThis followed similar defence
OL,12,Fsubmissions made this week by defence
OL,13,Fbarristers on behalf of all the
OL,14,Faccused.
OL,16,FAt the conclusion of the defence's
OL,17,Fsubmissions, Mrs Justice Smyth
OL,18,Fexpressed her gratitude to all counsel
OL,19,Finvolved and reserved judgement.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
